## Overview

Sprint 24 converts free OpenAgent extension users into paying enterprise customers through two pillars:

1. **Thin CSPM**: Replace the mock scanner with real AWS STS AssumeRole + top-20 Prowler-equivalent checks. Position cloud posture as an extension of agent risk.
2. **Enterprise Agent Dashboard**: Plan enforcement, alert dispatch, cross-linkage, risk trends, PDF reports, scheduled scans, and UI completeness.

### Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| AWS SDK approach | Modular AWS SDK v3 with `nodejs_compat` | Modular imports keep bundle under 1MB; fallback to SigV4 `fetch` if incompatible |
| PDF generation | `jspdf` + `jspdf-autotable` | Pure JS, works in Workers, ~300KB, sufficient for data tables |
| Plan enforcement | Reusable middleware factory | `requirePlanFeature()` / `requirePlanLimit()` avoids duplicating checks in every route |
| Alert dispatch | `ctx.waitUntil()` async fire-and-forget | Does not block sync response; failures logged but non-fatal |
| Cross-linkage | Query-time heuristic matching | No schema changes; simple LIKE queries on resource identifiers |
| Risk snapshots | Daily cron + time-series table | D1-compatible; batched writes stay within Worker limits |

