## Architecture

### High-Level System Architecture

Sprint 24 adds six new services, two new database tables, two altered tables, one new middleware factory, seven new API route files, and six new proxy routes to the existing architecture. All changes follow the established Hono middleware chain pattern.

```
Request Flow:
  Client -> CORS -> TokenForge -> RateLimiter -> Route Handler
                                                      |
                                              dbMiddleware
                                              authMiddleware
                                              resolveOrgContext / requirePermission
                                              requirePlanFeature (NEW)
                                              requirePlanLimit (NEW)
                                                      |
                                              Route Logic -> DB / Services
```

### Technology Stack Additions

| Layer | New Dependency | Purpose | Size Impact |
|---|---|---|---|
| Backend | `@aws-sdk/client-sts` | STS AssumeRole | ~70KB |
| Backend | `@aws-sdk/client-s3` | S3 checks | ~90KB |
| Backend | `@aws-sdk/client-iam` | IAM checks | ~80KB |
| Backend | `@aws-sdk/client-ec2` | EC2/VPC/SG checks | ~100KB |
| Backend | `@aws-sdk/client-rds` | RDS checks | ~60KB |
| Backend | `@aws-sdk/client-cloudtrail` | CloudTrail checks | ~50KB |
| Backend | `@aws-sdk/client-guardduty` | GuardDuty check | ~50KB |
| Backend | `jspdf` | PDF generation | ~300KB |
| Backend | `jspdf-autotable` | PDF tables | ~50KB |
| Frontend | `recharts` | Risk trend charts | ~180KB (tree-shaken) |

**Estimated total bundle increase**: ~850KB (compressed ~350KB). Stays well within the 10MB Worker bundle limit.

