## API Design

### New Endpoints

#### FR-3: Alert Channel CRUD

**File**: `apps/api/src/routes/agent-alert-channels.ts`

```
GET    /api/agents/alert-channels           List org alert channels
POST   /api/agents/alert-channels           Create alert channel
PATCH  /api/agents/alert-channels/:id       Update alert channel
DELETE /api/agents/alert-channels/:id       Delete alert channel
POST   /api/agents/alert-channels/:id/test  Send test notification
```

**Middleware**: `dbMiddleware, authMiddleware, requirePermission('agent.policy.write'), loadPlanConfig, requirePlanFeature('policyEngine')`

GET uses `requirePermission('agent.policy.read')` instead.

**Request Schema (POST /alert-channels)**:

```typescript
const createChannelSchema = z.object({
  channelType: z.enum(['email', 'slack', 'pagerduty', 'opsgenie', 'teams', 'discord']),
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  config: z.record(z.unknown()), // Validated per channel type below
  minSeverity: z.enum(['critical', 'high', 'medium', 'low']).default('high'),
  isActive: z.boolean().default(true),
});
```

**Per-Channel Config Schemas**:

```typescript
const emailConfigSchema = z.object({
  recipients: z.array(z.string().email()).min(1).max(10),
});

const slackConfigSchema = z.object({
  webhookUrl: z.string().url().startsWith('https://hooks.slack.com/'),
});

const pagerdutyConfigSchema = z.object({
  routingKey: z.string().min(1),
});

const opsgenieConfigSchema = z.object({
  apiKey: z.string().min(1),
  region: z.enum(['us', 'eu']).default('us'),
});

const teamsConfigSchema = z.object({
  webhookUrl: z.string().url(),
});

const discordConfigSchema = z.object({
  webhookUrl: z.string().url().startsWith('https://discord.com/api/webhooks/'),
});
```

**Response (POST)**:

```json
{
  "data": {
    "id": "uuid",
    "orgId": "org-uuid",
    "channelType": "slack",
    "name": "Security Alerts",
    "minSeverity": "high",
    "isActive": true,
    "createdAt": "2026-03-02T00:00:00.000Z",
    "updatedAt": "2026-03-02T00:00:00.000Z"
  }
}
```

Note: The `config` field is never returned in API responses. It is encrypted at rest and only read internally by the alert dispatch service.

**Request Schema (PATCH /alert-channels/:id)**:

```typescript
const updateChannelSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1).max(100).optional(),
  config: z.record(z.unknown()).optional(),
  minSeverity: z.enum(['critical', 'high', 'medium', 'low']).optional(),
  isActive: z.boolean().optional(),
});
```

