## Integration Points

### AWS STS AssumeRole

| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| Service | AWS STS |
| Auth | Cross-account IAM role with external ID |
| Duration | 900 seconds (15 min minimum) |
| Error handling | Catch `AccessDenied`, `MalformedPolicyDocument`, `RegionDisabledException` |
| Credentials | Never stored, never logged; used only during scan execution |

**Customer IAM Policy Template** (provided in docs):

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [{
    "Effect": "Allow",
    "Action": [
      "s3:GetPublicAccessBlock", "s3:GetBucketAcl",
      "s3:GetBucketVersioning", "s3:GetBucketLogging", "s3:ListAllMyBuckets",
      "iam:GetAccountSummary", "iam:GetAccountPasswordPolicy",
      "iam:ListUsers", "iam:ListMFADevices",
      "iam:ListPolicies", "iam:GetPolicyVersion", "iam:ListAccessKeys",
      "cloudtrail:DescribeTrails",
      "ec2:DescribeSecurityGroups", "ec2:DescribeVolumes",
      "ec2:GetEbsEncryptionByDefault", "ec2:DescribeVpcs",
      "rds:DescribeDBInstances",
      "guardduty:ListDetectors"
    ],
    "Resource": "*"
  }]
}
```

### Resend Email API

| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| Env var | `RESEND_API_KEY` (already configured) |
| Endpoint | `https://api.resend.com/emails` |
| From | `OpenSyber Security <security@opensyber.cloud>` |
| Rate limit | 100 emails/day (free tier), 1000/day (pro) |

### Slack Webhooks

| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| Stored in | `alert_channels.config` (encrypted) |
| Format | Block Kit JSON |
| Timeout | 5 second fetch timeout |
| Retry | No retry on failure (logged only) |

### PagerDuty Events API v2

| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| Endpoint | `https://events.pagerduty.com/v2/enqueue` |
| Auth | Routing key in config |
| Severity mapping | critical/high -> critical, medium -> warning, low -> info |

### OpsGenie Alert API

| Aspect | Detail |
|---|---|
| Endpoint | `https://api.opsgenie.com/v2/alerts` (US) or `https://api.eu.opsgenie.com/v2/alerts` (EU) |
| Auth | `GenieKey` header |
| Priority mapping | critical -> P1, high -> P2, medium -> P3, low -> P5 |

---

## Security Considerations

### Credential Storage

| Data | Storage | Encryption |
|---|---|---|
| Cloud account role ARN | `cloud_accounts.role_arn` | Plaintext (not secret) |
| Cloud account external ID | `cloud_accounts.external_id` | Plaintext (not secret alone) |
| Alert channel webhook URLs | `alert_channels.config` | AES-GCM via `encrypt()` |
| Alert channel API keys | `alert_channels.config` | AES-GCM via `encrypt()` |
| AWS STS temp credentials | In-memory only | Never stored, never logged |

### Access Control Matrix

| Endpoint | Auth | RBAC | Plan Gate |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST /agents/activity/sync | Clerk JWT | resolveOrg | cloudSync, agentLimit |
| GET /agents/team/* | Clerk JWT | agent.policy.read | teamDashboard |
| POST /agents/alert-channels | Clerk JWT | agent.policy.write | policyEngine |
| POST /cloud/accounts | Clerk JWT | cloud.write | cspmAccounts limit |
| POST /agents/reports/generate | Clerk JWT | agent.policy.read | pdfReports |
| POST /cloud/accounts/:id/scan | Clerk JWT | cloud.write | cspmAccounts > 0 |

### Confused Deputy Prevention

The `externalId` parameter on STS AssumeRole prevents confused deputy attacks. Each cloud account has a unique `externalId` generated at creation time. The customer's IAM trust policy must include a condition matching this `externalId`.

### Input Validation

All new endpoints use Zod schemas for request validation. The Zod schemas are defined at the top of each route file. No user input reaches the database without validation.

### Rate Limiting

| Resource | Limit | Implementation |
|---|---|---|
| Scan trigger per account | 5 per hour | KV counter with TTL |
| Alert dispatch per channel | 10 per minute | KV counter with 60s TTL |
| Activity sync | 200 events per request | Validated in handler |
| Scheduled scans per cron | 5 accounts per invocation | LIMIT clause |

---

## Performance Considerations

### D1 Query Optimization

| Query | Optimization |
|---|---|
| Risk trend (user) | `idx_risk_snapshots_user_date` composite index; simple range scan |
| Risk trend (org) | `idx_risk_snapshots_org_date` composite index; simple range scan |
| Alert channels for dispatch | `idx_alert_channels_org_active` filtered index |
| Activity sessions grouping | Fetch max 5000 events, group in JS; acceptable for single-user history |
| Cross-linkage LIKE queries | Bounded by max 5 results; LIKE on small result sets |
| Retention purge | Delete per-user with compound condition; batched by user |

### Cron Batching Strategy

| Cron Job | Batch Size | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Risk snapshots | 50 users per batch | Each user requires 2 queries (events + findings) |
| Scheduled scans | 5 accounts per invocation | Each scan involves multiple AWS API calls |
| Activity retention | 1000 users, delete per-user | DELETE is a single query per user |

### Bundle Size Management

AWS SDK v3 modules are imported individually to enable tree-shaking. Only the specific command classes needed are imported:

```typescript
// Good: individual imports
import { S3Client, GetPublicAccessBlockCommand } from '@aws-sdk/client-s3';

// Bad: full client import
import * as S3 from '@aws-sdk/client-s3';
```

If the total bundle size with all 7 AWS SDK clients exceeds comfortable limits, the fallback plan is to use raw `fetch` calls with AWS SigV4 signing via `@smithy/signature-v4`.

### Worker CPU Budget

| Operation | Estimated CPU time | Within 30s limit? |
|---|---|---|
| Activity sync (100 events) | ~50ms | Yes |
| Plan enforcement middleware | ~10ms (one DB query) | Yes |
| AWS scan (20 checks) | ~5-20s (mostly I/O wait) | Yes, borderline |
| PDF report generation | ~2-5s | Yes |
| Risk snapshot cron (50 users) | ~10-15s | Yes |
| Scheduled scan cron (5 accounts) | ~25s | Tight; parallelize I/O |

