## Testing Strategy

### Test Organization

Every new service and route file has a co-located test file.

```
apps/api/src/
  middleware/
    plan-enforcement.test.ts
  routes/
    agent-alert-channels.test.ts
    agent-risk-trend.test.ts
    agent-sessions.test.ts
    agent-team-user.test.ts
    agent-activity-findings.test.ts
  services/
    aws-scanner/
      index.test.ts
      s3-checks.test.ts
      iam-checks.test.ts
      ec2-checks.test.ts
      rds-checks.test.ts
      cloudtrail-checks.test.ts
      guardduty-check.test.ts
    alert-dispatch.test.ts
    activity-cspm-linker.test.ts
    risk-snapshot-cron.test.ts
    pdf-report-generator.test.ts
    cspm-scan-scheduler.test.ts
    activity-retention-cron.test.ts
```

### Unit Tests

#### Plan Enforcement Middleware

```typescript
describe('plan-enforcement', () => {
  describe('requirePlanFeature', () => {
    it('allows request when feature is enabled', async () => {
      // Setup: user on pro plan, feature: cloudSync = true
      // Expect: next() called, 200 response
    });

    it('returns 403 with upgrade message when feature is disabled', async () => {
      // Setup: user on free plan, feature: cloudSync = false
      // Expect: 403 with upgradeRequired: true
    });

    it('handles all 4 plan tiers correctly', async () => {
      // Test each feature gate across free/personal/pro/team
    });
  });

  describe('requirePlanLimit', () => {
    it('allows when under limit', async () => {
      // Setup: user has 2 agents, limit is 10
      // Expect: next() called
    });

    it('returns 403 when at or over limit', async () => {
      // Setup: user has 10 agents, limit is 10
      // Expect: 403
    });
  });
});
```

#### AWS Scanner Checks

Each check module has tests that mock AWS SDK responses:

```typescript
describe('s3-checks', () => {
  it('detects bucket without public access block', async () => {
    // Mock: ListBuckets returns 1 bucket
    // Mock: GetPublicAccessBlock throws NoSuchPublicAccessBlockConfiguration
    // Expect: 1 finding with checkId S3-PUB-BLOCK
  });

  it('passes bucket with all public access blocked', async () => {
    // Mock: GetPublicAccessBlock returns all true
    // Expect: 0 findings
  });

  it('handles API error gracefully', async () => {
    // Mock: ListBuckets throws AccessDenied
    // Expect: CheckResult with error field, no crash
  });
});
```

#### Alert Dispatch

```typescript
describe('alert-dispatch', () => {
  it('sends to all active channels matching severity', async () => {
    // Setup: 2 channels (Slack critical, email high), violation is critical
    // Expect: both channels receive alert
  });

  it('skips channels below severity threshold', async () => {
    // Setup: channel minSeverity=critical, violation is medium
    // Expect: no dispatch
  });

  it('respects rate limit per channel', async () => {
    // Setup: 11 violations in 1 minute
    // Expect: only 10 dispatched, 1 skipped
  });

  it('continues on individual channel failure', async () => {
    // Setup: Slack webhook returns 500
    // Expect: error logged, no throw, other channels still process
  });
});
```

### Integration Tests

#### Route Tests

Following the established pattern with `app.request()` and mock DB queues:

```typescript
describe('GET /api/agents/risk-trend', () => {
  it('returns 30-day trend for authenticated user', async () => {
    // Setup: mock auth, 30 snapshot rows
    // Expect: 200 with data array of 30 points
  });

  it('returns 401 for unauthenticated request', async () => {
    // Expect: 401
  });

  it('respects days query parameter', async () => {
    // Setup: ?days=7
    // Expect: data filtered to last 7 days
  });
});
```

### Coverage Targets

| Module | Target | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Plan enforcement middleware | 100% | Revenue-critical path |
| AWS scanner checks | 90% | Security-critical; edge cases are complex |
| Alert dispatch | 90% | Enterprise-critical; multiple channel types |
| Route handlers | 85% | Standard CRUD with auth/plan checks |
| PDF generator | 80% | Output format testing is limited |
| Cron jobs | 80% | Tested via service unit tests |
| Frontend skeletons | 70% | Visual components; snapshot tests sufficient |

