## Implementation Order

The recommended implementation order optimizes for unblocking dependencies and quick wins.

### Phase 1: Foundation (Days 1-3)

| # | Task | FR | Est |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Create migration 0013 + Drizzle schemas | DB | 0.5d |
| 2 | Implement plan enforcement middleware | FR-2 | 1d |
| 3 | Add missing API endpoints (sessions, team user) | FR-5 | 1d |
| 4 | Add missing proxy routes | FR-6 | 0.5d |

### Phase 2: Core Features (Days 4-8)

| # | Task | FR | Est |
|---|---|---|---|
| 5 | Loading skeletons for all pages | FR-10 | 0.5d |
| 6 | Plan enforcement on activity sync + all routes | FR-2 | 1d |
| 7 | Real AWS CSPM scanner (all 20 checks) | FR-1 | 3d |
| 8 | Alert dispatch service + channel CRUD | FR-3 | 1.5d |

### Phase 3: Enhancement (Days 9-12)

| # | Task | FR | Est |
|---|---|---|---|
| 9 | Risk trend time series (cron + API + chart) | FR-7 | 1.5d |
| 10 | Scheduled CSPM re-scan | FR-9 | 0.5d |
| 11 | Activity-CSPM cross-linkage | FR-4 | 1d |
| 12 | PDF report export | FR-8 | 1d |

### Phase 4: Polish + Testing (Days 13-14)

| # | Task | FR | Est |
|---|---|---|---|
| 13 | Activity retention cron | FR-2 | 0.5d |
| 14 | Integration tests for all new routes | All | 1d |
| 15 | UI polish: upgrade CTAs, empty states | All | 0.5d |

### Critical Path

```
Migration 0013 -> Plan Middleware -> Activity Sync Enforcement -> AWS Scanner -> Alert Dispatch
                                  -> Missing Endpoints/Proxies -> Skeletons -> Cross-linkage
                                  -> Risk Trend Cron -> Scheduled Scans
                                  -> PDF Reports
```

