## Appendices

### Design Decisions Log

| # | Decision | Options Considered | Choice | Rationale |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| DD-1 | AWS SDK in Workers | SDK v3 / SigV4 fetch | SDK v3 with `nodejs_compat` | Maintainability; fallback to fetch if incompatible |
| DD-2 | PDF generation | @react-pdf / jspdf / client-side print | jspdf + autotable | Pure JS, works in Workers, server-side download |
| DD-3 | Risk trend storage | Materialized view / Time-series table | Dedicated table with daily cron | D1 has no materialized views; cron is idempotent |
| DD-4 | Cross-linkage | Sync-time / Query-time | Query-time | Avoids slowing sync; heuristic matching improves over time |
| DD-5 | Alert dispatch | Synchronous / Async waitUntil | waitUntil | Does not block sync response; failure is non-fatal |
| DD-6 | Channel config storage | Separate KV / D1 encrypted | D1 encrypted column | Consistent with existing credential storage pattern |
| DD-7 | Plan check caching | Per-request / Per-session | Per-request via c.set() | Workers are stateless; one DB query per request is acceptable |
| DD-8 | Scanner error handling | Fail-all / Partial results | Partial results | A single failed check should not invalidate the entire scan |

### Conventions

- All new files follow `kebab-case.ts` naming
- All new route files export a named Hono instance (e.g., `export const agentAlertChannelRoutes = new Hono<...>()`)
- All new services use the `Db = DrizzleD1Database<Record<string, unknown>>` type alias
- All new API responses use `{ data }` on success, `{ error, message }` on failure
- All timestamps are ISO 8601 strings in UTC
- All IDs are UUID v4 via `crypto.randomUUID()`
- All encrypted fields use the existing `encrypt()`/`decrypt()` utility with `ENCRYPTION_KEY`

### Dependencies Added

| Package | Version | Purpose | Dev/Prod |
|---|---|---|---|
| `@aws-sdk/client-sts` | ^3.x | STS AssumeRole | prod |
| `@aws-sdk/client-s3` | ^3.x | S3 checks | prod |
| `@aws-sdk/client-iam` | ^3.x | IAM checks | prod |
| `@aws-sdk/client-ec2` | ^3.x | EC2/VPC checks | prod |
| `@aws-sdk/client-rds` | ^3.x | RDS checks | prod |
| `@aws-sdk/client-cloudtrail` | ^3.x | CloudTrail checks | prod |
| `@aws-sdk/client-guardduty` | ^3.x | GuardDuty check | prod |
| `jspdf` | ^2.x | PDF generation | prod |
| `jspdf-autotable` | ^3.x | PDF tables | prod |
| `recharts` | ^2.x | Trend charts (frontend) | prod |

### wrangler.toml Changes

```toml
# Add nodejs_compat for AWS SDK v3
compatibility_flags = ["nodejs_compat"]

# Add cron trigger if not already present
[triggers]
crons = ["*/5 * * * *"]  # Every 5 minutes
```

### Environment Variables (No New Secrets)

All required environment variables are already configured:
- `ENCRYPTION_KEY` -- for encrypting alert channel configs
- `RESEND_API_KEY` -- for email alerts
- `STORAGE` -- R2 binding for PDF reports

No new Cloudflare secrets are required. Slack webhooks, PagerDuty routing keys, and OpsGenie API keys are stored per-org in the `alert_channels` table, encrypted with the existing `ENCRYPTION_KEY`.
